\taxon{Construction}
\title{Quasi-coherent ideals for affine schemes}
\import{macro}

\p{
  Let #{I} be an ideal of a distributive lattice #{D}. We construct a sheaf of ideal #{\qsi{I}} on #{\spec D} as follows: For any #{a\in D}, we define 
  ##{ \qsi{I}(a) := a \wedge I. }
  Evidently, #{a \wedge I \subseteq D/a} is an ideal for all #{a\in D}. This is a sheaf of ideals of #{\rg{D}} by the same proof as \ref{schm-ZBG1}.
}